  <thing id="ioSGAltrAd" name="Altar of Adjustment" description="Description\nAn altar of adjustment is a massive wood and stone table, with a granite top, large iron rings set into each corner, and sturdy frame and panels of ebony wood. Most are covered in runes of pain, doubt, change, and rebirth.\n\nThe magic of the altar affects only helpless creatures laying on  its surface (normally tied there). Once an hour, such a creature can be asked a question. The creature must either answer the question to the best of its ability (without half-truths or dissemination), or make a DC 15 Fortitude saving throw. On a failed saving throw, a creature takes 1d4 Constitution damage. If a creature is ever drained to 0 Constitution by this item, its Constitution returns to full, its alignment changes to match whoever last asked it a question, and it becomes helpful to that creature. This effect cannot be reversed without the use of atonement, remove curse, greater dispel magic, or similar magic. \n\n{b}Construction Requirements{/b}: Craft Wondrous Item, {i}charm monster{/i}, {i}ghoul touch{/i}, {i}speak with dead{/i}; Cost: 36,400 gp\n\n{b}Note:{/b} This thing has not been fully implemented yet." compset="Wondrous" holdable="no">
